<HL>
   Spiegel Earnings Up
</HL>
<DATE>
07/25/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4
</SO>
<CO>
   SPGLA
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   OAK BROOK, Ill. -- Spiegel Inc. said second-quarter profit
rose 15% on a 23% increase in revenue.
   The catalog retailer reported earnings of $7.7 million, or
15 cents a share, compared with $6.7 million, or 13 cents a
share, a year earlier. Revenue rose to $403.7 million from
$327.6 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   John J. Shea, chief executive officer, said he sees
"significant opportunities for growth" despite "an extremely
competitive" retail environment that he expects to continue
through the end of the year.
</TEXT>
